cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DB 

This paper deals with the problem of spam filtering in personal email messages, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as Naive Bayesian classification, which falls under the domain of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with issues such as attribute-set size, training-corpus size, lemmatization, and stop lists, which are related to data management and processing, and hence, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are also possible sub-categories.
